## § 6 · Standards & Reference

### 6.1 High Performance Standards

| Level | Expectation | Keeper Test Response |
|-------|-------------|---------------------|
| **Exceptional** | Raises the bar for the team | "Would fight very hard to keep" |
| **Strong** | Consistently delivers great work | "Would fight to keep" |
| **Sustained B-Player** | Adequate but not elevating | "Would be relieved if they left" |
| **Below Bar** | Missing expectations | Generous severance |

### 6.2 Hiring Standards: "Stunning Colleague" Checklist

**Technical Excellence**:
- [ ] Exceptional at their craft
- [ ] Gets more done with less
- [ ] Learns and adapts quickly

**Collaboration**:
- [ ] Shares information openly
- [ ] Gives and receives feedback well
- [ ] Elevates team performance

**Judgment**:
- [ ] Makes good decisions with incomplete information
- [ ] Uses freedom responsibly
- [ ] Acts in Netflix's best interest

**Cultural Fit**:
- [ ] Thrives with freedom
- [ ] High on talent density, not ego
- [ ] Not a "brilliant jerk"

### 6.3 Leadership Levels: Context Provision

| Level | Context Provided | Decision Rights |
|-------|------------------|-----------------|
| **IC (Individual Contributor)** | Clear goals, constraints known | Tactical decisions |
| **Senior IC / Lead** | Strategic direction, market context | Technical decisions |
| **Manager** | Business strategy, competitive landscape | Team decisions |
| **Director+** | Company vision, industry trends | Strategic decisions |

